postcontent: Well no holds barred here. This is the best there is in .223, a Sig Sauer 556. With steel construction, variable gas porting, gas piston design, 6 point collapsible and folding stock, battery storage in butt, latching storage space in handle, magazine coupler built in, integral Picatinny, and BUIS as part of the gun, this is one of the most robust and dependable .223 rifles out there today. I have added some quality aftermarket components; A Surefire tail cap actuated L1 Lumamax two level brightness LED light, it is mounted in a Viking Tactic side mount. A Grip Pod System genuine, grip pod not a cheep knock off. And an EOTech 552 NV compatible revision F holographic weapon sight, powered by 2 AA batteries, with extras in the stock. This is a serious assault/battle rifle, sling mounts are built in and ready for any sling of your choosing. Couple extra magazines, maybe one or two of the new Surefire 60 or 100 rounders, drop bipod, set up shop, and become a one man road block. This gun takes standard AR-15 magazines and has become the new standard of reliability solving many of the issues that plagued the AR designs. Folds up small enough to throw in the trunk or back seat, and has been a well proven design for years now. I am in most need of cash but might consider a trade, particularly a good 1911 or AK but I am up to other offers, let me know the worst I can say is no. Thanks for the look.

title: For Trade:  GP WASR 10/63 AK47
postcontent:
*FTF in the Seattle area only*
Buyer must be over 18 and show Washington or military ID

This is a very good example of what a WASR can be when it's built right. 
No canted gas block or front sights. A little bit of mag wobble with empty steel mags, but that goes away once the mag is loaded. Less than 400 rounds through it. I have had 0 malfunctions with it, and have cleaned/lubed it after every shooting session. I have only used new-manufactured steel-cased ammo and haven't put anything corrosive through it. It's been well taken care of.

Romanian-made receiver. New Romanian-made chrome-lined barrel in very very excellent shape. Front trunnion shows that the parts kit was from 1982. Front trunnion also has the triangle/arrow stamping; means that the parts are from a de-milled military rifle (better quality than early WASRs, not leftover junk).  Has a Tapco G2 trigger group. Definitely one of the better WASRs around.

Comes with:
-6 steel mags
-Romanian mag pouch
-Butt-stock cleaning kit, cleaning rod, and oiler
-Bayonet
-Ghetto-rigged canvas/carabiner/paracord sling (in true third-world fashion!)
-A few boxes of Brown Bear FMJs

title: For Sale:  Walther PP - .32 - SOLD PENDING FUNDS
postcontent:
Hello.  I'm listing my blued Walther PP chambered in .32.  This Walther was made in France by Manurhin following World War II.  

Pistol does have slight holster wear, but is otherwise in very good condition.  It comes with one Walther magazine.  No box or papers.

No trades at all please.

Please email if interested.  Thank you.

Here's a little more information about Manurhin Walther PP's for those of you who may be interested. Walther licensed production of the PP series pistols to Manurhin in 1952. The Manurhin continued to manufacture the PP series until 1986. In fact, all postwar European-made PP series pistols manufactured until 1986 were manufactured by Manurhin, even though the pistol slide may bear the markings of the Walther factory in Ulm.

Magazine is correctly unnumbered (but Waa marked) and is a genuine WWII P38 magazine made by Mauser Waffenfabrik. Gun has the typical thin finish and rough machining Spreewerke P38s are known for. I bought it from the great grandson of the GI who brought it back from WWII. He did not keep it oiled and it exhibits some scattered light freckling, but is still in very good condition and all original. The bore is very good with nice rifling and a bit of scattered, very light pitting - just enough to keep me from calling it excellent. Still an above-average bore. Excellent mechanics and will make someone an excellent shooter, if you so desire. $625 firm face to face in Hickory, NC or possibly Winston Salem (I get there regularly).

title: For Sale:  Custom Stainless Springfield 1911A1 .45ACP
postcontent:
Custom Springfield 1911A1 Stainless Steel for sale or possible trade + cash for Rock Island brand or better 1911's in 9mm, 10mm, .40, or 45. Any size.

This weapon is in 95% condition.

It has a very low round count, with very little wear and strong lands and grooves to back it up.

It has been upgraded with all high quality brand replacement parts from Ed brown, and Wilson Combat.

It will come with 2 8rd mags, and 1 10rd mag, and rug.

It has the following upgrades:

1. Stainless steel compensator bushing, made to follow the profile of the slide.
2. Wilson Combat stainless steel full length guide rod.
3. Ed Brown stainless steel beavertail.
4. Ed Brown stainless steel Commander hammer.
5. Wilson Combat lightweight 3 hole trigger.
6. Ed Brown stainless steel extended slide release.
7. Ed Brown stainless steel magwell.
8. Simonich Gunner Grips MCSOCOM DET1 G10 grips.
9. Ed Brown stainless steel flat mainspring housing.
10. Wilson Combat stainless steel extended magazine release.

All work was done by Gunsmoke Guns outside Denver Colo. when I was stationed in the Army close to there several years ago. If you are ever by there you should stop in and check it out. It is quite the gun store. And now I guess they have a TV show.

Parts and labor to fit and install cost 550.00. Base pistol price was 700.00. Total 1250.00. Selling for 875.00

If you can buy the basic pistol and parts for alot cheaper, and put the parts on yourself, THEN DO IT. Dont whine and cry about the price of this pistol, because you really want this gun, but dont want to give what I want for it, or even come close. 
Pistols like this dont turn into turds, and become worthless after 500 rds and 7 years of flawless maintenance.

This pistol is more for the person who appreciates a fine weapon, and is NOT a wannabe gunsmith, or hobbyist, who does not care that labor costs money. Sure, you can look up parts prices on Ebay, etc. all day and do figuring and come up with a lower price, but, that does not reflect what you pay when you have it all dealt with at the same reputable place. When you buy the pistol at a gun store and have them order, then fit and install the parts, it costs money. I have found several real gunsmiths right now that charge 75.00 just to install a beavertail, not to mention the 8 other upgrade parts on this pistol, so it adds up. In the end, buying a pistol like this with what it has for the price is a great deal, looks and operates top notch, and it is ready to go and shoot, with no waiting or spending more money. Most people, like myself, are not gong to disassemble a gun beyond cleaning and try to do this themselves, as one small mistake can possibly cost someones well-being or life, or render the gun useless and worthless. 

I made the mistake of buying one of these Armlist Wichita wannabe gunsmith's firearms, (and they know who they are) who stated that it had been Duracoated, and had a trigger job, when in fact it had been spray painted, and filed a bit, which after shooting a few hundred rounds, the paint that made it inside the receiver of the weapon started to come off causing the internals to gum and seize up and the weapon catastrophically failed. A costly lesson learned. If the listing says Duracoated and you go to look at it, have a quick smell, if it smells like spray paint, it is. True Duracoat is an epoxy type coating and does not in any way smell like spray paint. Also, your fingernail will not affect a Duracoat finish in the slightest.

Pretty firm on the price, this is a nice 45, ready to go. Might have a little leeway, if I dont have to drive anywhere.

This is a private sale with no paperwork or FFL, unless you have it shipped. Will ship to FFL. Buyer pays shipping.

I am not really looking for any trades, but might entertain 1911 9mm, 10mm/.40, .45 trades. Rock Island brand or better. + cash.

Email if interested. I'm not in a hurry to sell and am not hard up for cash.
